description:
Over ons: **Let's build your future together!**  

Bij Prodware bouw je aan impactvolle AI\-oplossingen die écht het verschil maken voor onze klanten. Jouw werk helpt organisaties slimmer, aantrekkelijker en efficiënter te worden door het gebruik van innovatieve AI\-technologieën. Je stelt medewerkers in staat om zich te richten op taken met de hoogste toegevoegde waarde, terwijl AI hen ondersteunt bij dagelijkse werkzaamheden.





Jouw bijdrage heeft directe invloed op de groei, het succes en de innovatiekracht van onze klanten. Je werkt samen met gemotiveerde collega’s die technologie inzetten om bedrijven sterker te maken en innovatie tastbaar te realiseren. Hierbij maak je gebruik van de nieuwste AI\-technologieën van Microsoft, zoals Copilot, Copilot Studio en Azure AI.



Help ons de wereld van morgen vorm te geven als

**Technical** **AI Consultant**

Jouw verantwoordelijkheden:
* Ontwerpen, ontwikkelen en technisch implementeren van intelligente AI\-oplossingen op maat voor klanten;
* Zorgen voor een solide technische configuratie en implementatie van innovatieve AI\-oplossingen;
* Oplossen van complexe technische uitdagingen en continue optimalisatie van de prestaties van AI\-applicaties;
* Intensief samenwerken met functionele collega’s en klanten om opdrachten succesvol af te ronden;
* Werken binnen een Agile/Scrum\-omgeving en gebruikmaken van Azure DevOps voor CI/CD, versiebeheer en backlogmanagement.



Wat bieden wij  

* Uitdagende projecten bij toonaangevende klanten;
* Een dynamische werkomgeving met veel ruimte voor persoonlijke en professionele groei;
* Marktconform salaris en uitstekende secundaire arbeidsvoorwaarden;
* Mogelijkheid om certificeringen te behalen met ondersteuning zoals trainingen en een opleidingsbudget, en bij te dragen aan innovatieve oplossingen.

Wat breng je mee:
* Een afgeronde Bachelor of Master opleiding, of gelijkwaardige professionele ervaring;
* Minimaal 2 jaar relevante werkervaring als technisch consultant of in een vergelijkbare functie;
* Basiservaring met Microsoft Copilot, Copilot Studio, Azure AI en het Power Platform;
* Uitgebreide programmeerervaring met C\# of Python;
* Grondige kennis van ontwikkeling, training, configuratie en implementatie van AI\-modellen;
* Praktijkervaring met Large Language Models (LLMs) en Retrieval\-Augmented Generation (RAG);
* Certificeringen zoals Azure AI Engineer Associate (AI\-102\) of Azure Developer Associate (AZ\-204\) zijn een pré;
* Flexibiliteit, doorzettingsvermogen en een oplossingsgerichte mindset;
* Uitstekende communicatieve vaardigheden en een echte teamspirit;
* Beheersing van Nederlands en Engels in woord en geschrift. Een derde taal is een pré.



Wil jij deel uitmaken van ons team en ons helpen bedrijven naar de digitale toekomst te leiden?
Neem contact met ons op of stuur je sollicitatie naar recruiter@prodware.nl.  

We kijken ernaar uit je te ontmoeten!  

\#LI\-LT1

Do you have SaaS product management experience and are passionate about GenAI and prompting? Do you love staying up to date on all the latest AI trends, prompting and prompt optimisation strategies and techniques, and how they can automate and augment workflows? Do you want to test and learn using this knowledge in your daily PM work? Would you like to help build the future of AI Native customer engagement? If yes, keep reading as you could become an important member of Trengo’s talented and influential Product team and a crucial part of Trengo’s growth in the coming years! **This is where YOU come in!**
At Trengo, we believe in a world where technology empowers the relationship between companies and their customers. That’s why our mission is to build anAI\-powered customer engagement platformto replace repetitive work with meaningful conversations. How do we do that? Our software makes it easy for customer\-facing teams to communicate with customers via multiple channels, all in one shared inbox. Email, Instagram, Facebook, WhatsApp, live\-chat, you name it. With aSeries A investment of $36Mled by Insight Partners and Peak Capital and becoming one of the fourofficial WhatsApp Business Solutions Providersin the Netherlands, we empower our customers to scale their businesses and optimize the channels their clients truly prefer. **What you’ll be doing**
### **AI Fist Product Management:**

* Using AI tools and techniques for everything \- when they’re already mature and helpful, but also when they’re new and unknown … test the limits and learn;
* Working closely with Product Designers and Engineers to identify and deliver new functionality that solves our customers problems;
* Working in a collaborative, AI\-first, test \& learn, and highly agile manner;
* ProSetting clear expectations with stakeholders and keeping the broader teams informed and inspired;
* Identifying new opportunities with your team by understanding customer, user, and market requirements;
* Striving to create an environment of innovation, collaboration, and continuous improvement within the team and across the business.

### **AI Empowered Feature Development:**

* Distilling complex needs into effective prompts that ensure customers get more value from our product (AI agents, for example);
* Testing and iterating prompts and prompt chains for your own domains and in collaboration with others \- focusing on collaboration and knowledge sharing for this rapidly evolving field (GenAI and how to ensure prompts produce quality results);
* Staying up\-to\-date with the latest advancements in AI, determining what is relevant for our product (and product management), and sharing this with your colleagues.

### **What you’ll bring**

* Ability to demonstrate;
* A high level of knowledge and proficiency in writing and optimising prompts for various use cases and with multiple LLMs/model or;
* A a strong base in prompting, a passion for and strong interest in learning more, and the aptitude for rapid test and learn progress;
* High level of English and strong communication and stakeholder management skills. Customer centricity and an impact driven mindset.
* An adaptable and pragmatic mindset that allows you to embrace change and prefer progress over perfectionism.
* Experience in SaaS organisation, preferably in a senior role.
* 2\+ years’ experience as a product owner or product manager in a SaaS startup or scale\-up.

### **What we offer**

* This is what we carefully prepared for you:
* Finding yourself in a **fast\-growing company** where your career can evolve. With the help of your number one supporter, your manager, you will follow our departmental growth tracks to pursue the career you want. This is one of the reasons for our positive Glassdoor reviews(4/5\).
* We really value flexibility and trust our people. That’s why we work **hybrid,** and our people can **work from** **abroad for 60 days per year.**
* Free sessions with on\-demand psychologists from**OpenUp****.** Your mental health is important to us.
* An education budget to feed your curiosity,extra budget for team trainings, and 2 extra days off for your courses or conferences, if needed.
* **28 vacation days** to rest, have fun, and travel as you wish. But, every once in a while, we also like to do it together. The last time, we went on an amazing trip to Valencia!
* Internet and phone allowance every month!
* **Fancy learning Dutch?** We also offer Dutch courses for our international employees!
* When you work from our beautiful office: you can bet we have delicious warm lunches together prepared by our in\-house chef and workplace experience team. Also, your traveling expenses to Utrecht will be reimbursed.


Job descriptions can be difficult to interpret. If you believe you're a strong fit for the AI Native Product Manager role but don’t meet every requirement, we’d love to hear about your motivation in a cover letter!
